19:28.501 --> 19:29.960
- Let me see that.
- No.

19:30.127 --> 19:33.505
- Let me see it.
- What? It's a sweater. I was cold.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.423
Where did you get it?

19:35.591 --> 19:38.009
It's none of your business.
I got it from a friend...

19:38.177 --> 19:40.679
...who gave it to me for Christmas.

19:41.722 --> 19:43.974
That's a Lanvin sweater, Tanya.

19:44.141 --> 19:46.518
- Do you even know what a Lanvin is?
- Yeah, I know.

19:46.686 --> 19:49.062
Of course I know what a Lanvin is.

19:49.230 --> 19:51.857
Then you know you can't afford it.

19:52.024 --> 19:54.109
And neither can any of your friends.

19:54.527 --> 19:55.944
Um...

19:56.112 --> 19:58.613
You don't know who my friends are.

19:58.781 --> 20:01.741
Really. And Frances can afford it.

20:02.201 --> 20:04.286
That's right, that Frances.

20:04.453 --> 20:06.705
Frances gave you a Lanvin sweater?

20:06.873 --> 20:10.500
Yes, she did. She gave it to me
when I went over to her house...

20:10.668 --> 20:13.378
...to talk business.
I found her address and I went over...

20:13.546 --> 20:16.423
...and I brought lyric croissants
and I took a chance...

20:16.591 --> 20:19.217
...and I saw this look in her eye
and I think I sold her.

20:19.385 --> 20:21.094
Lenore, I sold her on Ray.

20:21.262 --> 20:23.638
You saw Frances behind my back?

20:23.806 --> 20:25.348
Yeah.

20:28.436 --> 20:29.436
So?

20:30.521 --> 20:31.646
Wow.

20:33.524 --> 20:37.402
I mean, I didn't do it to be mean. I'm trying
to be collaborative with you and Ray...

20:37.570 --> 20:39.696
It's okay. I'm just disappointed.

20:39.864 --> 20:42.032
- That's all.
- Wait.

20:42.199 --> 20:46.202
Something tells me you're not
gonna enjoy that sweater, T-Brain.

20:46.746 --> 20:50.332
It's bad karma and the color's all wrong
for your complexion.

21:14.023 --> 21:15.398
Darb.

21:16.150 --> 21:18.652
I've been thinking about
what you said the other day.

21:18.819 --> 21:21.488
About how I live my whole life
through men.

21:21.656 --> 21:25.075
Yeah, I... I wasn't trying to hurt you.

21:25.242 --> 21:26.618
Oh, I know.

21:27.536 --> 21:29.204
Anyway, I forgive you.

21:29.956 --> 21:34.292
- I didn't say I was sorry.
- Yeah, but you probably will.

21:34.460 --> 21:37.796
I'll just have to wait 20 years
and I don't want to be hurt that long...

21:37.964 --> 21:40.966
...so I'm gonna forgive the future you,
that delightful person...

21:41.133 --> 21:42.717
...who's gonna come to me and say:

21:42.885 --> 21:46.137
"Mom, I'm so sorry I gave you so much crap
when I was 16.

21:46.305 --> 21:50.767
I had no idea what life was like
or how hard it would be."

21:52.395 --> 21:55.605
Well, thanks for the ride.

21:55.773 --> 21:57.941
Oh, it's a pretty cake.

21:58.109 --> 22:00.986
What's it for anyway?
Somebody's birthday at the mall?

22:01.153 --> 22:03.196
Can you pick me up after 7?

22:05.616 --> 22:07.283
Be well.

22:10.663 --> 22:12.539
[WOMEN SHOUTING]

22:12.790 --> 22:14.791
WOMAN 1: I love my curvy hips.
WOMAN 2: Yeah!

22:14.959 --> 22:16.835
WOMAN 1:
I love my big ass.

22:17.003 --> 22:20.463
I am not lazy. I am not stupid.

22:20.631 --> 22:23.258
Go and stuff your judgment.

22:23.426 --> 22:25.844
I feel beautiful and I am beautiful.

22:26.012 --> 22:29.180
I don't want to diet. I don't need to diet.

22:29.348 --> 22:32.017
Because a diet is a cure
that doesn't work...

22:32.184 --> 22:34.978
...for a disease that doesn't exist.
ALL: Doesn't exist!

22:35.146 --> 22:37.480
I love my big butt.

22:37.648 --> 22:41.609
WOMEN [CHANTING]:
I love my big ass. I love my big butt.

22:41.777 --> 22:43.570
- Who is that?
- I love my curvy hips.

22:43.738 --> 22:45.572
- I love my big ass.
- My mom.

22:45.740 --> 22:47.657
- I'm sorry.
- I love my big butt.

22:47.825 --> 22:50.285
Hi, hey, hi.

22:50.453 --> 22:52.662
- You were supposed to pick me up at 7.
- I know.

22:52.830 --> 22:54.998
I was going to leave
but I had to come over...

22:55.166 --> 22:57.208
...and see what all the hoopla was about.

22:57.376 --> 22:59.461
Oh, heard the cheering.
What a great speaker.

22:59.628 --> 23:01.504
She's so moving.

23:02.590 --> 23:04.966
- Is this some sort of club meeting?
- Mom.

23:05.134 --> 23:07.343
Can you meet me in the car
in, like, 20 minutes?

23:07.511 --> 23:11.431
- It's a movement.
- Like for black people, but for fat people.

23:11.891 --> 23:14.100
- You girls aren't fat.
GIRL: Yes, we are.

23:14.268 --> 23:17.687
We're beautiful. We're fat
and there's nothing wrong with it.

23:17.855 --> 23:19.522
Okay.

23:19.690 --> 23:21.399
Offer your mom some cake.

23:21.567 --> 23:24.778
- She doesn't want any cake.
- Sure, she does.

23:24.945 --> 23:27.822
Mrs. Drecker, can I offer you
a piece of Darby's cake?

23:27.990 --> 23:31.409
Nope. And it's Haxon now. Mrs. Haxon.

23:31.577 --> 23:34.579
- Just let her be.
- Why don't you want the cake?

23:34.747 --> 23:35.747
I had a late lunch.

23:35.915 --> 23:36.956
[GIRLS CHUCKLING]

23:37.124 --> 23:38.833
JESSICA:
Why is that funny? What's so funny?

23:39.001 --> 23:41.669
- I don't understand.
- No, Mom...

23:41.837 --> 23:43.546
It's nothing. It's just...

23:43.714 --> 23:46.591
It's something that skinny people say.

23:47.134 --> 23:48.843
No, I did. At Bennigan's.

23:49.011 --> 23:52.514
Soup, half salad, dressing on the side.

23:52.848 --> 23:54.432
JESSICA:
I swear I'm just not hungry.

23:59.814 --> 24:01.898
Want me to eat the cake?
I'll eat the cake.

24:02.066 --> 24:05.235
- I'm gonna eat the cake.
- Mom, forget the cake, okay?

24:05.402 --> 24:06.861
Just go home.

24:07.029 --> 24:08.780
WOMEN: Fat, so what?
- Go.

24:09.490 --> 24:11.407
Fat, so what?

24:11.575 --> 24:15.328
Fat, so what? Fat, so what?

24:15.496 --> 24:17.372
Fat, so what?

24:17.540 --> 24:22.127
Fat, so what? Fat, so what?

24:34.431 --> 24:36.307
LENORE [ON RECORDING]:
If you've got an itch...

24:36.475 --> 24:37.642
...you know where to scratch.

24:37.810 --> 24:40.895
Hi, it's Jessica. Call me.

24:46.193 --> 24:47.527
[SIGHS]

24:56.829 --> 24:58.246
Hi.

24:59.081 --> 25:02.709
- Look, I'm sorry if I made you mad.
- No, it's fine.

25:02.877 --> 25:05.920
People argue.
At least you're not depressed.

25:06.630 --> 25:09.716
- Want some wine?
- Yeah.

25:09.884 --> 25:11.467
Look...

25:12.595 --> 25:14.929
It's easy to say the word "ex."

25:15.431 --> 25:18.391
"My ex-wife. My ex-husband."

25:18.559 --> 25:21.895
But you might find you don't like the way
it feels after a little while.

25:24.481 --> 25:28.526
Claire, you have a chance
to have a family.

25:29.111 --> 25:31.362
Lenore said you wouldn't
talk about this anymore.

25:31.530 --> 25:34.199
I know, but you... You think I'm so great?

25:34.366 --> 25:36.409
You think I'm so different
than your husband?

25:36.577 --> 25:41.497
- I don't know you, that's what's nice.
- I'm telling you. I let people down every day.

25:41.665 --> 25:45.293
There are people depending on me
right now and I'm late...

25:45.753 --> 25:47.045
...because I'm here.

25:47.213 --> 25:51.674
I had a wife too, and I wish
I'd fought harder to keep her.

25:53.761 --> 25:56.137
I don't want what happened to me
to happen to you.

25:57.223 --> 25:59.849
I don't want to do this
with you anymore.

26:01.602 --> 26:03.353
I'm leaving.

26:03.979 --> 26:07.190
And I think you should give your husband
another chance.

26:11.237 --> 26:13.947
It's not because I don't like you.

26:14.114 --> 26:16.282
I don't care if you like me or not.

26:18.285 --> 26:20.161
I'm not stupid.

26:21.163 --> 26:23.289
I know what I'm paying you for.

26:35.594 --> 26:37.387
Thousand dollars to stay.

26:38.222 --> 26:40.682
I'm gonna cook
some macaroni and cheese...

26:40.849 --> 26:44.477
...then we are gonna sit
and watch TV and eat it.

26:45.020 --> 26:47.522
And then later we'll go upstairs.

26:49.024 --> 26:51.234
And it'll be great.

26:57.366 --> 26:58.992
Thousand bucks.

27:00.035 --> 27:01.703
Last time.

27:07.960 --> 27:09.961
Make it 1200.

27:14.300 --> 27:16.009
RAY:
Sometimes when you try to sleep...

27:16.176 --> 27:18.803
...your mind races
a million miles an hour.

27:20.806 --> 27:22.682
And you can't shut it off.

27:24.476 --> 27:27.895
You can't sleep no matter
how exhausted you are.

27:28.647 --> 27:30.356
But sometimes...

27:30.899 --> 27:33.109
...those rare lucky times...

27:34.028 --> 27:37.739
...you just lay down and forget it all.

27:39.533 --> 27:42.994
And sometimes a mattress
is just a mattress.

27:43.746 --> 27:46.331
And it feels fucking great.
